    "Name": "Mackenzie",
    "Details": "Defiance Industries has used the Mackenzie as a dedicated testing platform for ballistic weaponry for years, most recently as part of development testing for the Hyper Gauss Rifle in conjunction with Clan Jade Falcon. While the weapon did eventually get manufactured, development took longer than initially expected and so the company wound up with an excess of testbed models which they then sold off after replacing the testing weaponry with production versions. The Mackensie is built around a torso cockpit and a 280-rated Extra-Light Fusion Engine for power. For backup weaponry, the Mackensie mounts an ER PPC and a quartet of Magshots. Four jump jets give it extra positioning ability.<br><br>S-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that substantially improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
